1
00:02:27,560 --> 00:02:29,900
[The Tower of Whispers]

2
00:02:30,000 --> 00:02:31,390
[Episode 8]

3
00:02:31,560 --> 00:02:32,360
Five,

4
00:02:32,590 --> 00:02:33,750
your knife skills are amazing.

5
00:02:33,750 --> 00:02:35,000
Five, you're incredible.

6
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:35,520
Yeah.

7
00:02:35,520 --> 00:02:36,360
Five.

8
00:02:36,360 --> 00:02:37,310
Really impressive.

9
00:02:37,310 --> 00:02:39,000
Well done.

10
00:02:39,000 --> 00:02:40,329
-My Lady.
-Look at this.

11
00:02:40,400 --> 00:02:41,680
Are you feeling better?

12
00:02:41,680 --> 00:02:42,610
Yes, better now.

13
00:02:42,680 --> 00:02:43,630
Thank you, Five.

14
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:44,680
You have the day off today.

15
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,210
I'll take you to the market.

16
00:02:46,520 --> 00:02:47,310
Let's go.

17
00:02:48,520 --> 00:02:49,280
Thank you.

18
00:02:49,280 --> 00:02:51,000
Five, see if there's anything you want.

19
00:02:51,000 --> 00:02:52,120
I'll buy it for you.

20
00:02:53,280 --> 00:02:54,800
Ring toss! Ring toss!

21
00:02:55,280 --> 00:02:56,840
Toss rings on beautiful porcelain.

22
00:02:56,840 --> 00:02:58,570
Win one and you've struck gold!

23
00:02:58,910 --> 00:02:59,520
Sir.

24
00:03:00,030 --> 00:03:00,840
Look, someone's going to play.

25
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:02,750
10 copper coins' worth of rings, please.

26
00:03:02,750 --> 00:03:04,280
Miss Lu, it's you again.

27
00:03:04,360 --> 00:03:05,120
What?

28
00:03:05,360 --> 00:03:07,150
Still after my big horse today?

29
00:03:07,280 --> 00:03:08,310
I knew it.

30
00:03:08,310 --> 00:03:10,360
The magpies were chattering this morning.

31
00:03:10,360 --> 00:03:12,710
So Miss Lu has come to offer me money.

32
00:03:13,400 --> 00:03:14,530
Here are your rings.

33
00:03:15,590 --> 00:03:17,360
Today I've brought help with me.

34
00:03:17,360 --> 00:03:19,620
Your prized horse won't be safe anymore.

35
00:03:20,840 --> 00:03:22,570
Help me win that biggest horse.

36
00:03:26,750 --> 00:03:27,560
Childish.

37
00:03:29,520 --> 00:03:30,560
I paid 10 copper coins for these.

38
00:03:30,560 --> 00:03:32,150
How could you just
toss them so carelessly?

39
00:03:32,150 --> 00:03:32,800
Got it!

40
00:03:32,800 --> 00:03:33,840
Amazing!

41
00:03:33,840 --> 00:03:34,590
That's impressive!

42
00:03:34,590 --> 00:03:35,800
Incredible!

43
00:03:36,630 --> 00:03:37,800
He got them all!

44
00:03:38,680 --> 00:03:39,960
How did he do that?

45
00:03:40,910 --> 00:03:42,280
That's too incredible!

46
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,000
This...

47
00:03:47,079 --> 00:03:48,960
How did he win so many things?

48
00:03:49,470 --> 00:03:51,280
Which one should I take?

49
00:03:52,150 --> 00:03:53,470
How about this, Miss Lu?

50
00:03:53,470 --> 00:03:54,670
You take the big horse

51
00:03:54,840 --> 00:03:55,800
and leave the small ones

52
00:03:55,800 --> 00:03:56,840
for me.

53
00:03:56,840 --> 00:03:59,150
Weren't you
talking about chattering magpies?

54
00:03:59,150 --> 00:04:00,870
I've spent so much money
in vain at your stall.

55
00:04:00,870 --> 00:04:01,710
You're still trying

56
00:04:01,710 --> 00:04:03,310
to take advantage of me
for these little things?

57
00:04:03,310 --> 00:04:04,560
The big horse is mine,

58
00:04:04,560 --> 00:04:06,290
and the rest go to the children.

59
00:04:07,030 --> 00:04:07,960
Thank you, miss.

60
00:04:08,120 --> 00:04:09,360
Don't thank me.

61
00:04:09,560 --> 00:04:10,950
Thank that gentleman over there.

62
00:04:10,950 --> 00:04:11,390
Go on.

63
00:04:11,390 --> 00:04:12,450
Thank you, mister.

64
00:04:12,630 --> 00:04:14,070
Thank you, mister.

65
00:04:14,070 --> 00:04:15,130
Thank you, mister.

66
00:04:16,070 --> 00:04:16,870
You're amazing!

67
00:04:16,870 --> 00:04:17,560
Miss Lu.

68
00:04:17,950 --> 00:04:18,680
Here's your horse.

69
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:19,950
Thank you.

70
00:04:22,390 --> 00:04:23,510
I want this one!

71
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,360
I want this one!

72
00:04:24,360 --> 00:04:25,040
One at a time.

73
00:04:25,040 --> 00:04:26,000
One by one.

74
00:04:26,000 --> 00:04:26,950
One at a time.

75
00:04:28,630 --> 00:04:29,800
Why are you so happy?

76
00:04:30,630 --> 00:04:32,159
It's just a ceramic horse.

77
00:04:32,630 --> 00:04:34,680
The valuable things at your Lu's Mansion

78
00:04:34,680 --> 00:04:35,680
are far more than this.

79
00:04:35,680 --> 00:04:36,610
It's different.

80
00:04:36,950 --> 00:04:38,310
Don't you find it fun?

81
00:04:39,040 --> 00:04:40,170
What's fun about it?

82
00:04:50,159 --> 00:04:51,070
It's your turn.

83
00:04:51,270 --> 00:04:52,310
Try to imitate it.

84
00:04:57,560 --> 00:04:58,950
Alright, I won't laugh at you.

85
00:04:58,880 --> 00:05:00,410
♪ I heard that in the spring of '64 ♪

86
00:05:01,780 --> 00:05:03,100
♪ The wind rose at the mountain gate ♪

87
00:05:03,890 --> 00:05:05,020
♪ Strange tales unfold in a book ♪

88
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:07,140
♪ Recording their story ♪

89
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,480
I'd like 2 candy figurines please.

90
00:05:07,820 --> 00:05:09,300
♪ Ridiculous words ♪

91
00:05:08,750 --> 00:05:09,560
Alright.

92
00:05:09,980 --> 00:05:12,980
♪ Hastily blaming the cruelty of time ♪

93
00:05:13,710 --> 00:05:14,980
♪ Yet it still knocks
on my heart and soul ♪

94
00:05:15,500 --> 00:05:16,350
♪ Like a dream from another life ♪

95
00:05:16,800 --> 00:05:17,870
Done. One for each of you.

96
00:05:16,930 --> 00:05:18,160
♪ Reincarnating in words ♪

97
00:05:17,870 --> 00:05:19,680
Okay, thank you.

98
00:05:19,370 --> 00:05:20,200
♪ Afraid others won't understand ♪

99
00:05:20,820 --> 00:05:23,260
♪ Afraid of stirring emotions
for no reason ♪

100
00:05:24,160 --> 00:05:29,580
♪ Better to have a beginning with no end ♪

101
00:05:33,430 --> 00:05:35,760
What is the Longxiang Guard even good for?

102
00:05:36,159 --> 00:05:38,270
A pleasure boat caught fire
in the inner city last night.

103
00:05:38,270 --> 00:05:39,950
My uncle was burned to death.

104
00:05:40,510 --> 00:05:41,560
Such a major incident,

105
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:43,420
and I only found out this morning!

106
00:05:43,870 --> 00:05:44,720
It's my fault.

107
00:05:47,560 --> 00:05:48,310
Yan Hui,

108
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,720
my Investiture Ceremony
is approaching,

109
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,720
yet the city keeps

110
00:05:52,720 --> 00:05:54,320
having incidents like this.

111
00:05:54,480 --> 00:05:56,240
How can I be at ease?

112
00:05:56,240 --> 00:05:57,040
I understand.

113
00:05:57,430 --> 00:05:59,040
I will strengthen security in the city.

114
00:05:59,040 --> 00:06:00,070
I guarantee with my life

115
00:06:00,070 --> 00:06:01,310
that on the day of the ceremony,

116
00:06:01,310 --> 00:06:02,190
everything goes perfectly.

117
00:06:02,190 --> 00:06:02,830
Good.

118
00:06:03,600 --> 00:06:05,800
I know your loyalty and capability.

119
00:06:06,430 --> 00:06:07,430
From today,

120
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:10,230
I appoint you as
Commander of the Longxiang Guard.

121
00:06:10,240 --> 00:06:11,560
My Investiture Ceremony

122
00:06:11,560 --> 00:06:13,360
will be your full responsibility.

123
00:06:13,360 --> 00:06:14,800
But you have to find out

124
00:06:14,800 --> 00:06:16,390
who murdered my uncle Ding Huairen

125
00:06:16,390 --> 00:06:17,510
within 10 days.

126
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:18,750
Otherwise,

127
00:06:19,040 --> 00:06:20,840
I will have your entire Lu family

128
00:06:21,360 --> 00:06:23,040
executed.

129
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,730
Yes, Your Highness.

130
00:06:26,850 --> 00:06:28,760
[Lu's Mansion]

131
00:06:28,890 --> 00:06:31,470
[Ding Huairen
was burned to death at 9 p.m.]

132
00:06:30,190 --> 00:06:32,990
Ding Huairen was found
burned to death on the boat.

133
00:06:33,360 --> 00:06:35,360
Last night, 4 skilled guards
were escorting him

134
00:06:35,360 --> 00:06:36,720
when they passed Misty Willow Bridge

135
00:06:36,720 --> 00:06:38,310
and engaged in fierce combat.

136
00:06:38,020 --> 00:06:39,380
[Misty Willow Bridge]

137
00:06:39,360 --> 00:06:40,960
They all perished in the end.

138
00:06:43,950 --> 00:06:46,610
Witnesses say it was
a skilled fighter in white.

139
00:06:59,070 --> 00:06:59,750
How is it?

140
00:06:59,750 --> 00:07:02,280
This is the surprise
I prepared for you today.

141
00:07:03,430 --> 00:07:05,830
You have headaches, so I was worried
the fireworks would be too loud.

142
00:07:05,830 --> 00:07:08,830
I specifically had Cai Ping
set them off at a distance.

143
00:07:14,830 --> 00:07:16,830
How did you know about my headaches?

144
00:07:21,270 --> 00:07:23,070
I just guessed.

145
00:07:23,870 --> 00:07:25,480
But you're so young.

146
00:07:25,480 --> 00:07:27,480
How did you develop this condition?

147
00:07:28,990 --> 00:07:35,270
♪ Black hair turns to smoke,
love ends in sorrow ♪

148
00:07:29,600 --> 00:07:31,240
When I was little, my mother

149
00:07:31,800 --> 00:07:32,950
would soak me

150
00:07:34,120 --> 00:07:35,630
in medicinal baths on snowy days
to strengthen me.

151
00:07:34,420 --> 00:07:38,710
[Teenage Jun Che]

152
00:07:36,200 --> 00:07:42,470
♪ By the Naihe Bridge,
no one has perfect love ♪

153
00:07:37,680 --> 00:07:39,390
Mother!

154
00:07:40,000 --> 00:07:42,460
That's why my blood
has healing properties.

155
00:07:43,150 --> 00:07:50,180
♪ This life's fate is shallow, sighing,
love hard to explain ♪

156
00:07:43,800 --> 00:07:44,680
Since then,

157
00:07:44,680 --> 00:07:46,740
I've suffered from these headaches.

158
00:07:47,390 --> 00:07:47,920
Then

159
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:50,640
what does it feel like when it happens?

160
00:07:50,670 --> 00:07:56,590
♪ Before the Three Lives Stone,
time carved into light years ♪

161
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:52,430
Very painful.

162
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,530
Everything seems too loud,

163
00:07:54,750 --> 00:07:56,880
like someone is screaming and roaring

164
00:07:57,310 --> 00:07:58,120
inside my head.

165
00:07:57,340 --> 00:08:03,650
♪ When the lights first shine,
one glance from you feels like eternity ♪

166
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:02,800
It's fine.

167
00:08:03,240 --> 00:08:04,150
It's all in the past.

168
00:08:04,150 --> 00:08:10,650
♪ In front of the Buddha, devoutly,
stranded before the Forgetting River ♪

169
00:08:11,050 --> 00:08:18,250
♪ Three lifetimes searching,
only remembering your smile ♪

170
00:08:11,190 --> 00:08:12,590
This is the Calming Bead.

171
00:08:12,600 --> 00:08:13,950
My mother obtained it for me.

172
00:08:13,950 --> 00:08:14,800
It works very well.

173
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:16,480
If you keep it close to you,

174
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:17,630
I think those noises

175
00:08:17,630 --> 00:08:19,000
might become less noisy.

176
00:08:18,760 --> 00:08:25,970
♪ I would go against the heavens
to fulfill this love ♪

177
00:08:19,070 --> 00:08:20,200
This belongs to you.

178
00:08:20,310 --> 00:08:21,170
I can't take it.

179
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:24,800
Five, did you bring your dagger?

180
00:08:26,350 --> 00:08:32,440
♪ In a night, a single flower blooms;
In a moment, reincarnation fades ♪

181
00:08:32,950 --> 00:08:38,900
♪ I hope that in this life,
we never part again ♪

182
00:08:33,870 --> 00:08:35,000
It's yours now.

183
00:08:36,780 --> 00:08:39,159
[Five]

184
00:08:40,230 --> 00:08:47,010
♪ When will this love cease?
My heart is tied with a thousand knots ♪

185
00:08:44,360 --> 00:08:45,790
In this lifetime,

186
00:08:47,320 --> 00:08:48,720
will things be different for us?

187
00:08:48,310 --> 00:08:53,870
♪ The past is unforgettable ♪

188
00:08:54,870 --> 00:08:55,720
My Lady!

189
00:08:55,720 --> 00:08:56,440
Yingying!

190
00:08:56,870 --> 00:08:58,070
-My Lady!
-Yingying!

191
00:09:00,510 --> 00:09:01,080
Brother.

192
00:09:02,910 --> 00:09:03,670
Brother!

193
00:09:04,790 --> 00:09:07,990
What are your intentions
bringing Yingying here so late?

194
00:09:08,790 --> 00:09:09,550
My Lord,

195
00:09:10,270 --> 00:09:11,960
I am not your prisoner,

196
00:09:12,480 --> 00:09:14,940
and I don't like
having a knife pointed at me.

197
00:09:15,630 --> 00:09:17,240
Brother, you've really misunderstood.

198
00:09:17,240 --> 00:09:18,510
I asked him to come.

199
00:09:20,510 --> 00:09:21,770
Five, I'm warning you.

200
00:09:22,270 --> 00:09:23,670
You're just our family guard.

201
00:09:23,670 --> 00:09:25,080
Know your place,

202
00:09:25,270 --> 00:09:27,470
and stay away from Yingying from now on.

203
00:09:27,630 --> 00:09:28,840
Didn't I tell you?

204
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,670
I invited him to watch the fireworks.

205
00:09:30,670 --> 00:09:32,150
It's true. Trust me.

206
00:09:32,960 --> 00:09:33,720
Yingying,

207
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:34,790
the city isn't safe lately.

208
00:09:34,790 --> 00:09:35,480
There have been many murders.

209
00:09:35,480 --> 00:09:36,600
Don't go out this late anymore.

210
00:09:36,600 --> 00:09:37,150
Alright.

211
00:09:37,480 --> 00:09:38,550
I got it, Brother.

212
00:09:38,490 --> 00:09:41,470
[Lu's Mansion]

213
00:09:43,000 --> 00:09:43,790
Yingying!

214
00:09:43,960 --> 00:09:45,000
Father, Mother.

215
00:09:45,270 --> 00:09:46,960
Where have you been so late?

216
00:09:46,960 --> 00:09:48,320
I've been so worried.

217
00:09:48,670 --> 00:09:50,720
It's so dangerous for a young girl.

218
00:09:50,840 --> 00:09:53,080
Why are you still waiting for me so late?

219
00:09:53,080 --> 00:09:54,790
It's cold. Let's go inside.

220
00:09:54,790 --> 00:09:56,200
So you know it's late.

221
00:09:56,440 --> 00:09:58,900
You know your parents
are worried about you?

222
00:09:59,600 --> 00:10:01,240
Father, Mother, don't worry.

223
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:02,910
I'm fine. I'm safe.

224
00:10:04,630 --> 00:10:05,600
Was she

225
00:10:06,000 --> 00:10:07,480
with Five all day?

226
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,080
Father, no.

227
00:10:12,080 --> 00:10:13,240
When I found her,

228
00:10:13,270 --> 00:10:15,730
she was setting off fireworks
with Cai Ping.

229
00:10:19,510 --> 00:10:21,120
Father, Mother, let's go inside.

230
00:10:21,120 --> 00:10:22,480
I'm sorry. It's my fault.

231
00:10:22,480 --> 00:10:23,440
It won't happen again.

232
00:10:23,440 --> 00:10:24,510
You're not allowed
to come home this late anymore.

233
00:10:24,510 --> 00:10:26,150
Let's see if you dare do it again.

234
00:10:26,150 --> 00:10:27,030
I wouldn't dare.

235
00:10:27,030 --> 00:10:28,760
Your mother even cried for you.

236
00:10:33,840 --> 00:10:34,960
It's okay, Brother.

237
00:10:34,960 --> 00:10:36,480
Five's martial arts are excellent.

238
00:10:36,480 --> 00:10:38,200
I'm very safe with his protection.

239
00:10:38,200 --> 00:10:40,570
[Ding Huairen
was burned to death at 9 p.m.]

